about.summary: A set of tools for inspecting and understanding R data structures inspired by str(). Includes ast() for visualizing abstract  syntax trees, ref() for showing shared references, cst() for showing  call stack trees, and obj_size() for computing object sizes.

name: r-lobstr
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '1.1.1' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-lobstr
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/lobstr_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/lobstr/lobstr_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: b8c9ce00095bd4f304b4883ef71da24572022f0632a18c3e1ba317814e70716e

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}            # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}      # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-rcpp
    - r-crayon
    - r-rlang >=0.3.0
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-rcpp
    - r-crayon
    - r-rlang >=0.3.0

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('lobstr')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('lobstr')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/r-lib/lobstr
  license: GPL-3
  summary: A set of tools for inspecting and understanding R data structures inspired by str().
    Includes ast() for visualizing abstract  syntax trees, ref() for showing shared
    references, cst() for showing  call stack trees, and obj_size() for computing object
    sizes.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - philip-khor
